Stack 0: Intelligence Hub (The LLM Server)
This foundation stack provides centralized AI capabilities to all other services via the Shared Pipeline. It is optimized for local execution with strict resource management.

intelligence_hub (Ollama): The core LLM engine. It hosts multiple models and is configured with aggressive RAM management (OLLAMA_KEEP_ALIVE) and sequential processing (OLLAMA_MAX_LOADED_MODELS=1) to ensure system stability on hardware with limited CPU/GPU.

model_provisioner (Utility): An automated service that ensures the required models are pulled:
- nomic-embed-text: Specialized for high-precision vector embeddings.
- deepseek-r1:1.5b: Lightweight reasoning model for fast, edge-side summarization.
- llama3.2:3b: The "Student" model used for high-quality RAG answer generation.
- gemma2:2b: The specialized "Judge" model used for logical evaluation.

Stack 1: Data Ingestion & Storage (The Crawler System)
This stack is responsible for the Open/Closed Principle (OCP), allowing dev to add new scrapers without modifying the core storage logic.

news_db (MongoDB): The "Source of Truth" for the system. It stores raw and semi-structured article data. It uses JSON Schema Validation and limited cache (0.5GB) to ensure Data Integrity while freeing RAM for AI.

rabbitmq (Message Broker): Acts as the Interface Segregation layer. It decouples the Crawler from the RAG system. It coordinates data flow after the AI Agent has processed the content.

crawler_worker (Python AI-Agent): An intelligent scraper that follows the Single Responsibility Principle (SRP). It collects raw data, leverages the intelligence_hub (DeepSeek-R1) to generate concise summaries, persists the enriched data to MongoDB, and publishes events to RabbitMQ.

Stack 2: Intelligence & Retrieval (The RAG System)
This stack implements the CQRS (Command Query Responsibility Segregation) pattern by splitting the embedding logic from the user-facing search logic.

vector_db (Qdrant): The high-performance semantic index. It stores vector embeddings of the articles for fast similarity searches.

rag_ingestor (Worker Service): The "Command" side. It consumes messages from RabbitMQ, calls the intelligence_hub (nomic-embed-text) for embeddings, and writes to the Vector DB. This is Compute-intensive.

rag_query_api (FastAPI): The "Query" side. It handles incoming user requests, retrieves relevant context from the Vector DB, and interfaces with the intelligence_hub (Llama-3.2:3b "Student") to generate final answers. It is optimized for Low Latency.

Stack 3: Quality Assurance & Evaluation (The Evaluator System)
This stack follows the Dependency Inversion Principle (DIP), allowing you to swap out "Judge" models without breaking the test suite.

rag_evaluator (Evaluation Engine): A standalone service that runs the RAG Triad metrics (Faithfulness, Answer Relevance, Context Precision). It connects to the intelligence_hub (Gemma-2:2b "Judge") to evaluate the Student's performance.

eval_judge_llm (Local/External LLM): The model used as the "Teacher." By using gemma2:2b, the system leverages a specialized logical model to critique the more general llama3.2:3b student, creating the necessary intelligence gap for objective evaluation.